author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "how about make main_thread_handle as Option<Handle>?\r\n\r\nExcept creating a child process, it is difficult for us to get the main_thread_handle of another process. If we make this item Option, we could extend struct Process's use case. Such as building a process manager, which holds some process's handle without main_thread_handle.\r\n\r\n```rust\r\npub struct Process {\r\n    handle: Handle,\r\n    main_thread_handle: Option<Handle>,\r\n}\r\n\r\nimpl Process {\r\n    ...\r\n\r\n    pub fn main_thread_handle(&self) -> Option<BorrowedHandle<'_>> {\r\n        self.main_thread_handle?.as_handle()\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    ...\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nMaybe related to #96723 ", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/107144/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/107144/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}